AB  - This article studies different methods of assigning a good to budget-constrained agents. Schemes that assign the good randomly and allow resale may outperform the competitive market in terms of Utilitarian efficiency. The socially optimal mechanism involves random assignment at a discount—an in-kind subsidy—and a cash incentive to discourage low-valuation individuals from claiming the good.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rds025
